  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nsilent die of deploy ERC20 token from array\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nI try to deploy array of ERC20 tokens from tokens.json:\r\n```\r\n{\"XXXX\":{\"symbol\":\"XXX\", \"totAmount\": \"21000000\",  \"address\":\"\"}, \r\n\"YYYY\":{\"symbol\": \"YYY\", \"totAmount\": \"21000000\",  \"address\":\"\"},\r\n\"ZZZZ\":{\"symbol\":\"ZZZ\", \"totAmount\":\"21000000\", \"address\":\"\"},\r\n```\r\n\r\nwith code in migrations:\r\n```\r\nconst MockERC20 = artifacts.require('MockERC20.sol');\r\nconst tokens = require (\"../tokens.json\");\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = async function(deployer,_network, addresses) {\r\nconst admin = addresses[0];\r\nawait Object.keys(tokens).forEach (async (tokenName) => {\r\n  var token = tokens[tokenName];\r\n  const contERC = (tokenName, token, admin) => {\r\n  try { \r\n    if (token.address == '') {\r\n      const totAm = web3.utils.toWei(token['totAmount']);\r\n      return MockERC20.new (tokenName, token['symbol'], totAm, {from:admin});\r\n   } \r\n   else {\r\n      return MockERC20.at(token.address);\r\n     } \r\n   } \r\n  catch (e) {\r\n     console.log (e)\r\n}\r\n}\r\nconst contract = await contERC(tokenName, token, admin);\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd every way (in a lot of variants) got silent die (no post-mortem messages) at  \r\n`return MockERC20.new (tokenName, token['symbol'], totAm, {from:admin});`\r\n\r\ntest code like \r\n`return  MockERC20.new (“Nametoken”, “NTT”, “21000000”, {from:admin});`\r\n– don’t works too\r\n\r\nbut this test code outside  \r\n```\r\nObject.keys(tokens).forEach (async (tokenName) => {\r\n…\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n -  works properly, token deployed.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\nDeploy several ERC20 tokens \r\n## Actual Result\r\ntokens didn't deploy\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Linux Mint 19 \r\n* Ethereum client: Web3/ Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v5.1.67 (core: 5.1.67)\r\n* node version (`node --version`):  v12.14.1 (same behavior in 10.18 and 14.15)\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.13.4\r\n",
